00:00:11.990 --> 00:00:13.670
Riddle 1

00:00:13.670 --> 00:00:20.220
Imagine your self on a sinking boat
Surrounded with sharks, how do you survive?

00:00:21.050 --> 00:00:24.380
Stop imagining!

00:00:25.050 --> 00:00:27.320
Riddle 2

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:33.350
Lighter than feather, yet you can't hold it for long.

00:00:33.780 --> 00:00:37.560
Your breath.

00:00:38.160 --> 00:00:40.400
Riddle 3

00:00:41.260 --> 00:00:45.810
It doesn't have flesh, feathers, scales, or bones,
Yet it has fingers and a thumb.

00:00:46.130 --> 00:00:50.080
A glove.

00:00:50.960 --> 00:00:53.270
Riddle 4

00:00:54.010 --> 00:00:58.580
Black when you buy it, red when you use it,
Grey when you throw it away.

00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:02.900
Charcoal.

00:01:02.940 --> 00:01:05.880
Riddle 5

00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:11.160
Can you name three consecutive days
without mentioning: Sat, Sun, Mon, Tue, Thu or Fri?

00:01:11.640 --> 00:01:15.250
Yesterday, Today and Tomorrow.

00:01:15.960 --> 00:01:18.250
Riddle 6

00:01:18.760 --> 00:01:23.440
Filled with holes, Yet keeps water. What is it?

00:01:23.590 --> 00:01:27.390
A sponge.

00:01:27.900 --> 00:01:30.250
Riddle 7

00:01:30.650 --> 00:01:35.440
I have Forests without trees, Lakes without water,
Streets without cars. What am i?

00:01:35.650 --> 00:01:39.490
The map.

00:01:40.220 --> 00:01:42.380
Riddle 8

00:01:42.790 --> 00:01:47.600
I follow you everyday,
I leave you at night,
I vanish when clouds blocks the sun.

00:01:47.910 --> 00:01:51.720
Shadows.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:54.590
Riddle 9

00:01:55.030 --> 00:01:59.750
Eskimos are professional hunters,
But never hunt for penguines, why?

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:03.940
Eskimos live in North Pole,
Penguines live in South Pole.

00:02:04.510 --> 00:02:06.670
